 BY AKINWALE ABOLUWADE Some suspected herdsmen have reportedly killed a farmer named Musa Monsuro in Ibarapa Central Local Government Area of Oyo State. Report had it that Monsuro was slaughtered on his cashew farm at Araromi village, Igboora, around 5pm on Monday. Reason for the attack could not be immediately determined at the time of filing this report. It was, however, gathered that those behind the act were herdsmen. Policemen were said to have deposited the corpse at the mortuary. The Police Public Relations Officer, Oyo State Command, Adewale Osifeso, confirmed the incident. Osifeso was quoted as saying that “The case is undergoing investigation. You will be updated accordingly.” 